cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.LO, cs.CR 

This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to develop a system for proof guidance in first-order logic reasoning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of neural-based attention mechanisms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing and the use of logical formalisms, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), respectively. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the system's performance, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
